// END OF MOVEMENT II
//
// The chase has exhausted itself. The inverted theme — falling where it
// should rise — almost emerged in the final pages, but collapsed before
// completion. The tritone (F#-C) has done its destabilizing work; we end
// on an E minor that feels provisional, uncertain.
//
// Movement III, "Lacuna," will be the still point: after fog, after fever,
// a space of quiet. The cello will sing a long melody that contains all
// the theme's intervals in the wrong order — so close, yet not.
